<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-023-071 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 446 507</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Sources  Nov 1991 v2 n11 p57(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The action-packed DOS market. (product development of versions ofDOS from Microsoft Corp. and Novell Inc.) (Forum) (Brief Article)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pepper, Jon.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Product development)Novell Inc. (Product development)Digital Research Inc. (Acquisitions, mergers, divestments).andO;Ticker:    MSFT; NOVL.andO;Product:   MS-DOS 6.0 (Operating system) (Product development).andO;Topic:     Operating SystemsProduct DevelopmentMS-DOSNetwork Operating Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Windows 3.0 may be getting the bulk of the attention in the operating systemsmarket, but the world of PC operating systems is seeing plenty of actionthese days.andP;  No sooner did DOS 5.0 hit the streets when rumors about themakeup of DOS 6.0 began to circulate.andP;  Moreover, Novell--the major force inthe LAN market--recently acquired Digital Research (DRI), whose DR DOS 5.0holds a respectable 7 percent share of the worldwide PC operating systemmarket.andP;  What does all this mean for the near future of DOS?andM;First, Microsoft's DOS 5.0 still reigns supreme in the DOS market; Microsofthas set not delivery date for 6.0.andP;  And you shouldn't hold your breathwaiting for one, says Nancy McSharry of International Data Corp., a marketresearch company in Framingham, Massachusetts.andP;  &quot;I don't think Microsoft isclear about what they are doing [with 6.0andrsqb; yet, and I am sure that DOS 5.0will be a viable product for a good two years,&quot; she says.andP;  &quot;You can't domajor operating system upgrades often.&quot;andM;Brad Chase, Mirosoft's DOS product manager, confirms that the company isworking on verion 6.0, but says, &quot;We aren't saying anything about DOS 6.0since we just announced DOS 5.0.&quot;andM;However, if you're interested in early speculation about DOS 6.0, industryobservers say 6.0 features will include protected-mode 386 support that willallow true multitasking with DOS, advanced file management, and an enhancedability to load drivers into high memory beyond what DOS 5.0 can accomplish.andM;As for the merger of Novell and Digital Research, some industry watchers sayNovell intends to move into the operating system business with a new versionof DRI's DR DOS that combines the best features of NetWare and DR DOS.andP;  &quot;Iwouldn't at all be suprised to see a tightly integrated LAN operating systemthat is DOS compatible from Novell in the next 18 to 24 months,&quot; McSharrysays.andM;While many of these predictions will come to pass, they'll do so far in thefuture.andP;  They shouldn't hold up your current buying plans.andO;</TEXT></DOC>